org.opendaylight.controller.config.api.jmx

Interface ConfigRegistryMXBean

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ConfigRegistry, LookupRegistry, ServiceReferenceReadableRegistry
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConfigRegistryClient
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConfigRegistryJMXClient, TestingConfigRegistry

    public interface ConfigRegistryMXBean
extends ConfigRegistry
    Represents entry point of configuration management. Note: Reason for having methods in super interface is that JMX allows only one MXBean to be implemented and implementations can expose additional methods to be exported.
    Implementation of ConfigRegistry is not required to implement this interface, but is required to export all methods of ConfigRegistry to JMX so that this interface can be used as a proxy.
